1. Introduction
Purpose
The purpose of this Business Requirements Document (BRD) is to outline the requirements for developing a multi-functional automobile platform.
 This platform will serve as a comprehensive resource for information on automobile companies, car and bike models, comparisons, petrol
 pumps, spare parts, upcoming vehicles, news, car dealers, second-hand cars, and more. The goal is to provide users with an interactive
 and user-friendly platform for exploring and comparing automobiles and related services.

Scope
This document covers the functional and non-functional requirements for the development of the platform,
including system architecture, data requirements, integration needs, and user interface design.
It will guide the development, testing, and deployment phases of the project, ensuring that all
stakeholder needs are met.

Definitions and Acronyms
BRD: Business Requirements Document
API: Application Programming Interface
UI: User Interface
DB: Database
SLA: Service Level Agreement
2. Project Overview
Project Goals
Comprehensive Information: Provide detailed information about automobile companies, car and bike models, and petrol pumps.
Comparison Tools: Develop tools for comparing cars and bikes based on various attributes.
Dynamic Pricing: Implement a system for tracking and displaying dynamic petrol pump prices.
News and Updates: Offer up-to-date news and updates on the automobile industry.
User-Friendly: Ensure the platform is intuitive and accessible for all users.
Background
The automobile industry is rapidly evolving, with frequent updates on new models, technology advancements, and market trends. This project aims to consolidate information from various sources into a single platform, enhancing user experience and providing valuable insights into the automobile sector.

Stakeholders
Project Manager: Oversees project execution and coordination.
Development Team: Responsible for coding, integration, and system architecture.
QA Team: Handles testing and quality assurance.
End Users: Individuals accessing the platform for information and comparisons.
Business Analysts: Define requirements and ensure alignment with business goals.
3. Functional Requirements
Automobile Company
Overview: This section provides detailed profiles of various automobile companies.
Features:

Company Overview: Name, history, and key achievements.
Vehicle Range: List of vehicles manufactured.
Contact Information: Address, phone numbers, and website.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to view the profile of a specific automobile company to learn about their history and offerings.
Car Company
Overview: Information about car manufacturing companies.
Features:

Detailed Profiles: History, market position, and innovations.
Car Models: List of available car models and their specifications.
Reviews: User and expert reviews of the company’s vehicles.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to explore different car companies to find one that suits my needs.
Bike Company
Overview: Information about bike manufacturing companies.
Features:

Company Information: Background, achievements, and market presence.
Bike Models: List of bikes and their specifications.
User Reviews: Reviews and ratings from users.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to compare bike companies to find the best options available.
Car Comparison
Overview: A tool for comparing various car models.
Features:

Comparison Criteria: Specifications, features, and pricing.
Side-by-Side Comparison: Visual comparison of selected car models.
Filter Options: Filters for different criteria like price, engine type, etc.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to compare multiple cars to make an informed purchasing decision.
Bike Comparison
Overview: A tool for comparing different bike models.
Features:

Comparison Features: Specifications, performance metrics, and pricing.
Comparison Tool: Interactive tool for side-by-side comparison.
Filter Options: Filters for various criteria such as price range, engine capacity, etc.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to compare different bike models to determine which is best suited for me.
Petrol Pump
Overview: Information about petrol pumps including location and pricing.
Features:

Pump Locations: Interactive map of petrol pump locations.
Price Updates: Real-time updates on petrol prices.
User Reviews: Ratings and reviews from users.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to find petrol pumps near me and view current prices to plan my refueling.
Component Spare Parts
Overview: Information about spare parts for various vehicles.
Features:

Spare Part Catalog: List of available spare parts with details.
Availability Status: Information on stock levels.
Pricing: Price details for each spare part.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to search for and find spare parts for my vehicle.
Upcoming Cars
Overview: Information about upcoming car models.
Features:

Release Dates: Information on upcoming car releases.
Specifications: Details of the upcoming models.
Pre-Order Options: Information on how to pre-order or register interest.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to learn about new car models that will be available soon.
News
Overview: Latest news related to the automobile industry.
Features:

News Articles: Recent news articles with summaries.
Categories: News categorized by type (e.g., industry updates, new launches).
Search Functionality: Search bar to find specific news articles.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to stay informed about the latest news and trends in the automobile industry.
Car Dealers
Overview: Information about car dealers and their services.
Features:

Dealer Locations: Map of car dealer locations.
Services Offered: Details of services provided by each dealer.
Contact Information: Phone numbers and email addresses.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to find car dealers and get their contact details.
Second-Hand Cars
Overview: Information on certified pre-owned cars.
Features:

Listings: Details of available second-hand cars.
Certification Details: Information on the certification process.
Pricing: Price details and negotiation options.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to browse and compare certified pre-owned cars to find a good deal.
Automobile History
Overview: Historical data and information about automobiles.
Features:

Historical Timelines: Key events and milestones in automobile history.
Evolution: Development of automobile technology over time.
Important Figures: Information about influential people in automobile history.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to learn about the history and evolution of automobiles.
Petrol Pump Finder
Overview: Tool to find petrol pumps by state and city.
Features:

Location Search: Search for petrol pumps based on location.
Price Updates: Real-time price changes at different pumps.
Filters: Filters for state, city, and price range.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to search for petrol pumps in different locations and see their prices.
Insurance Companies
Overview: Information about insurance providers for automobiles.
Features:

Company Profiles: Details about insurance companies.
Policy Details: Information on different types of insurance policies.
Contact Information: Contact details for insurance companies.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to compare insurance policies from different providers.
Finance Companies
Overview: Information about finance companies offering loans for automobile purchases.
Features:

Company Profiles: Information about finance companies.
Loan Options: Details of loan products and terms.
Contact Information: Contact details for finance companies.
User Stories:
As a user, I want to compare financing options for purchasing an automobile.
4. Non-Functional Requirements
Performance
The system should support concurrent users without significant performance degradation.
Response times for queries and transactions should be within acceptable limits.
Security
User data must be protected using encryption and secure access controls.
Implement measures to prevent unauthorized access and data breaches.
Usability
The platform should have an intuitive user interface with easy navigation.
Ensure that users can perform tasks efficiently with minimal training.
Reliability
The system should be reliable with minimal downtime.
Implement failover mechanisms and backup procedures to ensure data integrity.
Scalability
The system should be scalable to handle increased load and data growth.
Design for horizontal and vertical scaling as needed.
5. Data Requirements
Data Models
AutomobileCompany: Fields include company name, history, and contact details.
CarModel: Fields include model name, specifications, and pricing.
BikeModel: Fields include model name, specifications, and pricing.
PetrolPump: Fields include location, price, and reviews.
SparePart: Fields include part name, availability, and price.
NewsArticle: Fields include title, content, and publication date.
Data Sources
Internal Databases: For storing company profiles, vehicle information, and user data.
External APIs: For real-time pricing, news updates, and external data integration.
Data Flow
Data Entry: Data is entered through user interfaces and integrated systems.
Data Processing: Data is processed and stored in databases.
Data Retrieval: Data is retrieved for display on the platform and for user interactions.
6. Integration Requirements
Internal Systems
Database Integration: Integration with internal databases for storing and retrieving data.
Authentication Systems: Integration with authentication systems for user login and registration.
External Systems
Third-Party APIs: Integration with APIs for real-time data (e.g., petrol prices, news feeds).
Payment Gateways: Integration with payment systems for transactions and purchases.
7. User Interface Design
Design Principles
Simplicity: The UI should be simple and easy to navigate.
Consistency: Maintain a consistent design language across the platform.
Responsiveness: Ensure the UI is responsive and works on various devices.
Wireframes
Homepage: Overview of all major sections with navigation options.
Car Comparison Tool: Interface for comparing car models side-by-side.
Petrol Pump Finder: Map and search interface for finding petrol pumps.
