Project Risks: Delays in development or changes in requirements.
Operational Risks: Issues with system uptime or user adoption.
Mitigation Strategies
Technical Risks: Implement robust testing and quality assurance processes.
Project Risks: Develop a clear project plan and manage changes effectively.
Operational Risks: Monitor system performance and have a support plan in place.
12. Acceptance Criteria
Success Criteria
Functionality: All specified features and functions are implemented and working.
Performance: The system meets performance and response time requirements.
User Satisfaction: Positive feedback from end-users during UAT.
Validation
Functional Testing: Ensure all functionalities meet the requirements.
Performance Testing: Validate system performance under expected load.
User Feedback: Collect and analyze user feedback to ensure satisfaction.
